namespace#OCS-doc
title#Office Coffee Standard (OCS)
version#v1.0.0-dev1
###
4#Programme requirements

4.1#General requirements

4.1#The organization shall establish a coffee programme that meets the requirements of this standard.

4.1#The programme shall cover sourcing, roasting, and quality assurance.

4.2#Bean sourcing

4.2#The organization shall source beans only from approved suppliers.

4.2#Approved suppliers shall be evaluated at planned intervals.

4.2#NOTE Supplier approvals may be time-limited and should be renewed before expiry.

4.2#EXAMPLE A typical approval window is 12 months, after which a reassessment is required.

4.3#Roast logging

4.3#Every roast batch shall be recorded with:

4.3#• batch identifier

4.3#• roast date and time

4.3#• roast level achieved

4.3#• bean lot identifier

4.3#NOTE Records may be electronic or paper-based.

4.3#EXAMPLE A minimum batch record contains the four fields above plus the roaster's initials.

4.4#Quality checks

4.4#Every batch shall be tested for moisture content before release.

4.4#Moisture content shall be between 8 percent and 12 percent by mass.

4.4#The organization shall define a freshness grade threshold and apply it consistently.

4.4#EXAMPLE A reading of 10.4 percent by mass is compliant at grade A.

4.4#EXAMPLE A reading of 11.6 percent by mass is compliant at grade C but not at grade A.
